{"questionId":"22646072","questionHtml":"<p>Find the probability that the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> has two <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-intercepts.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognizes that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>Z</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>Z</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>probability of two <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-intercepts is</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mi>Z</mi></mfenced><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>Z</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;or&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>Z</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;(can be shown on a labelled diagram)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><em>(A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>158655</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>158655</mn><mo>…</mo></math></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>Z</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;(can be shown on a labelled diagram)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbs